<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Lincheng/88: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-23T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">May 23,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 23—1
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>178. My 176, May 23, 3 p.m., paragraph 8. Diplomatic body at meeting this
                            afternoon adopted my suggestion of sending international commission to
                            Tsaochwang composed of military commanders at Tientsin or substitutes
                            named by the Legations concerned with instructions to investigate and
                            report upon military situation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
